{
  "text": "The positive linear relationship observed between Ba d and silicic acid throughout the global ocean (Fig. 6) Southern Ocean has been shown by numerous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ; data presented here for the Scotia Sea) to exhibit lower slopes and higher intercepts than are observed in other regions ( Fig. 6 ; Table 3 ).",
